{"title_page": "Dallupura", "text_new": "{{moresources|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Dallupura\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = [[Village]]\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Delhi#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Delhi, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|28.6004|N|77.3194|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Delhi]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[East Delhi]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_total        = 132628\n| population_as_of        = 2001\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]], [[English language|English]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 110096\n| registration_plate      = DL \n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\n\n'''Dallupura''' is a village on the outskirts of the [[East Delhi|Trans-Yamuna]] region of [[Delhi]], [[India]].  It is situated near [[Uttar Pradesh]] (UP) [[New Okhla Industrial Development Authority]](NOIDA) border alongside Vasundhra Enclave and Kondli. It is one of the 24 Dedha villages that are situated in the Trans Yamuna region.  Hindon canal runs along one side of the village. It is well connected to Noida, Ghaziabad and rest of the Delhi. It falls under Kondli legislative assembly constituency(Reserved) and East Delhi parliamentary constituency.\n\nThis village is surrounded by 56 CGHS Societies and has good infrastructure facilities. [[Dharamshila Hospital]] lies on the outskirts of the village. Four schools are adjacent to this village, namely [[Cosmos Public School]], Evergreen Public School, [[Somerville School]] and Starex International School. [[Maharaja Agrasen College]], affiliated to [[Delhi University]] (DU), is also situated in this region. The closest Metro station is 2&nbsp; km from the village. One is [[New Ashok Nagar Metro station]] and the other is [[Noida sec.15 Metro Station]]. Both are at equal distance from this village.\n\nWell known organization \u2018Child and Youth Welfare Society\u2019 registered here in and working Pan India and overseas for Social and Skill Development.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2001}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Dallupura had a population of 132,628. Males constitute 54% of the population and females 46%. Dallupura has an average literacy rate of 65%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 73% and, female literacy is 56%. In Dallupura, 15% of the population is under 6 years of age. Village dominated by dedha gurjars which comprises 90 percent of village population and 65 percent in the whole area of dallupura. Late Ch. Swaroop Singh Sarpanch was the Sarpanch of this village. He was a well known personality in the area nearby. [[Mukhiya Gurjar]],  another prominent Gurjar leader belongs to this village. [[Anand kumar]], son of late ch. swaroop singh sarpanch,is the councillor of this area.mr gaje singh bsp leader\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in East Delhi district]]\n[[Category:Villages in East Delhi district]]\n\n{{Delhi-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{moresources|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Dallupura\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = [[Village]]\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Delhi#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Delhi, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|28.6004|N|77.3194|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Delhi]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[East Delhi]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_total        = 132628\n| population_as_of        = 2001\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]], [[English language|English]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 110096\n| registration_plate      = DL \n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\n\n'''Dallupura''' is a village on the outskirts of the [[East Delhi|Trans-Yamuna]] region of [[Delhi]], [[India]].  It is situated near [[Uttar Pradesh]] (UP) [[New Okhla Industrial Development Authority]](NOIDA) border alongside Vasundhra Enclave and Kondli. It is one of the 24 Dedha villages that are situated in the Trans Yamuna region.  Hindon canal runs along one side of the village. It is well connected to Noida, Ghaziabad and rest of the Delhi. It falls under Kondli legislative assembly constituency(Reserved) and East Delhi parliamentary constituency.\n\nThis village is surrounded by 56 CGHS Societies and has good infrastructure facilities. [[Dharamshila Hospital]] lies on the outskirts of the village. Four schools are adjacent to this village, namely [[Cosmos Public School]], Evergreen Public School, [[Somerville School]] and Starex International School. [[Maharaja Agrasen College]], affiliated to [[Delhi University]] (DU), is also situated in this region. The closest Metro station is 2&nbsp; km from the village. One is [[New Ashok Nagar Metro station]] and the other is [[Noida sec.15 Metro Station]]. Both are at equal distance from this village.\n\nWell known organization \u2018Child and Youth Welfare Society\u2019 registered here in and working Pan India and overseas for Social and Skill Development.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2001}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Dallupura had a population of 132,628. Males constitute 54% of the population and females 46%. Dallupura has an average literacy rate of 65%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 73% and, female literacy is 56%. In Dallupura, 15% of the population is under 6 years of age.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in East Delhi district]]\n[[Category:Villages in East Delhi district]]\n\n{{Delhi-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "146.196.34.230", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dallupura"}
{"title_page": "Drumcreen", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Coord|54|25|28|N|7|34|38|W|display=title}}\n\n[[File:Road at Drumcreen - geograph.org.uk - 349703.jpg |thumb|right|Drumcreen, Northern Ireland]]\n\n'''Drumcreen, Northern Ireland''' is a locality and [[townland]] in [[Northern Ireland]]. The [[townland]] of Drumcreen is 123.37 [[acre]]s in [[area]]. Drumcreen is in the [[civil parish]] of [[Magheracross]], [[Barony of Tirkennedy]]. and [[County Fermanagh]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.townlands.ie/fermanagh/tirkennedy/magheracross/drumcreen/ | title=Drumcreen Townland, Co. Fermanagh | publisher=townlands.ie | accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{County Fermanagh}}\n\n[[Category:Townlands of County Fermanagh]]\n\n\n{{Fermanagh-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Coord|54|25|28|N|7|34|38|W|display=title}}\n\n[[File:Road at Drumcreen - geograph.org.uk - 349703.jpg |thumb|right|Drumcreen, Northern Ireland]]\n\n'''Drumcreen, Northern Ireland''' is a locality and [[townland]] in [[Northern Ireland]]. The [[townland]] of Drumcreen is 123.37 [[acre]]s in [[area]]. Drumcreen is in the [[Civil Parish]] of [[Magheracross]], [[Barony of Tirkennedy]]. and [[county]] of  [[Fermanagh]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.townlands.ie/fermanagh/tirkennedy/magheracross/drumcreen/ | title=Drumcreen Townland, Co. Fermanagh | publisher=townlands.ie | accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{County Fermanagh}}\n\n[[Category:Townlands of County Fermanagh]]\n\n\n{{Fermanagh-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Utopes", "label": "safe", "comment": "wikilink fixes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drumcreen"}
{"title_page": "Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu", "text_new": "{{Infobox military person\n| name          = Vatan Haini Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu\n| image         = Admiaral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu.jpg\n| birth_date    = September 4, 1965\n| birth_place   = [[Hakkari]], Turkey\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nickname      = \n| allegiance    = {{flag|Turkey}}\n| branch        = {{flagicon image|Flag of Turkish Naval Forces Command.PNG|size=18px}} [[Turkish Navy]]\n| serviceyears  = 1986\u20132016\n| rank          = [[Rear admiral]]\n| commands      = Turkish Mine Group<br>4th Destroyer Division<br>TCG Zafer (USS Tomas C. Hart)\n| battles       = [[Operation Active Endeavour]]<br>[[United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon]]<br>[[Operation Unified Protector]]\n| awards        = 3rd The Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition<br>5th The Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition\n| website       = \n}}\n\n'''Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu''' was a [[Two-star rank|two-star]] [[Rear admiral|admiral]] in the [[Turkish Naval Forces|Turkish Navy]] who recently served as a [[flag officer]] at [[NATO]] [[Allied Command Transformation|Supreme Allied Command Transformation]] in [[Norfolk, Virginia|Norfolk]]-[[United States|USA]].\n[[File:Admiral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu.jpg|right|thumb|250px|Admiral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu CO, Thomas C Heart (TCG ZAFER)]]\n\n== Navy career ==\n\nHe has been promoted to Rear Admiral (LH) in 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/turkey/2011/08/05/yas-promotes-36-generals-and-admirals-to-higher-rank|title=YA\u015e promotes 36 generals and admirals to higher rank|work=DailySabah|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> and Rear Admiral (UH) in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/2015-yuksek-askeri-sura-yas-kararlarini-acikladi-yas-kararlarinda-atama-alan-kisiler-kimler-29735528|title=2015 Y\u00fcksek Askeri \u015eura (YA\u015e) kararlar\u0131n\u0131 a\u00e7\u0131klad\u0131! YA\u015e kararlar\u0131nda atama alan ki\u015filer kimler?|work=H\u00fcrriyet|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr}}</ref> Before his last assignment in NATO,  He has served as Head of Communication and Information Systems Department<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.haber7.com/guncel/haber/911273-hangi-komutan-hangi-goreve-atandi-tam-liste|title=Hangi komutan hangi g\u00f6reve atand\u0131, tam liste|last=Haber7|website=Haber7|language=tr|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> between 2011 and 2012, Head of Personnel Department<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.haberler.com/atama-kararlari-11-3839329-haberi/|title=Atama Kararlar\u0131|work=Haberler.com|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr-TR}}</ref> between 2012-2013, and the Commander of Turkish Mine Group between 2013-2015.  He commanded [[Ottoman minelayer Nusret|Nusret]] 2013<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ege-sularinda-nefes-kesen-tatbikat-27657028|title=Ege sular\u0131nda nefes kesen tatbikat|work=H\u00fcrriyet|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr}}</ref> and Nusret 2014<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.denizhaber.com.tr/denizlerimizde-1-dunya-savasindan-kalma-200un-uzerinde-mayin-var-haber-58932.htm|title=Denizlerimizde 1. D\u00fcnya Sava\u015f\u0131'ndan kalma 200'\u00fcn \u00fczerinde may\u0131n var'|work=Deniz Haber|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr-TR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/nusret-2014-nefes-kesti-izmir-yerelhaber-493278/|title=NUSRET-2014 NEFES KEST\u0130|last=sitesi|first=milliyet.com.tr T\u00fcrkiye'nin lider haber|website=M\u0130LL\u0130YET HABER - T\u00dcRK\u0130YE'N\u0130N HABER S\u0130TES\u0130|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> international [[Minelaying|Mine Warfare]] exercises.\n\nAs a [[surface warfare officer]], he was assigned as Commanding Officer of TCG Zafer ([[USS Thomas C. Hart (FF-1092)|USS Tomas C. Hart]]) between 2005-2007 and Commander of 4th Destroyer Division between 2010-2011. He participated in the [[Operation Active Endeavour]] in 2006, [[United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon]] (UNIFIL) in 2007 and [[2011 military intervention in Libya|Non-Combatants Evacuation Operation of Libya]] in 2011.\n\nAshore, Ugurlu served at [[NATO]], [[Turkish General Staff]] and [[Turkish Naval Forces]] Headquarters as Naval Project & Planning Officer. During his NATO [[Allied Joint Force Command Naples|Allied Joint Forces Command]] Naples-Italy tour, he participated [[NATO#Kosovo intervention|Kosovo]] and [[NATO intervention in Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnia-Herzeginova]] operations between 2000 and 2003.\n\nHis assignment included a role as inspector officer for [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)]], where he executed monitoring mission in old [[Eastern Bloc]] Countries and participated in international inspections. \n\n== NATO and International Career ==\n\nHe served as Assistant Chief of Staff of Command & Control, Deployability and Sustainability in [[Allied Command Transformation|NATO Supreme Allied Command Transformation in Norfolk]], USA between 2015 and 2016. He was responsible for NATO\u2019s Cyber Defense, Big Data, Artificial Intelligence, Communication Information Systems, Space, [[Federated Mission Networking]], Core Enterprise Services, Ballistic Missile Defense programs.\n[[File:Admiral Ugurlu, Replenishment at sea during Libya Evacuation Operation (TCG Gaziantep and ITS Etna).jpg|left|thumb]]\nHe was a member of key NATO executive boards, including Consultation Command Control Board (C3B), Agency Supervisory Board (ASB), Cyber Defense Management Board (CDMB), and Capability Package Board (CPB).\n\nHe was Naval Planning Officer in [[Allied Naval Forces Southern Europe|NATO-AFSOUTH-Napoli]] between 2000-2003, he was responsible for developing maritime capabilities on NATO naval bases and facilities in the Mediterranean.\n\nHe was assigned as an inspector officer for [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)]], monitoring missions in old Eastern Bloc Countries, as well as participated in international inspections with European partners between 1998-2000.\n\nHe have participated in international operations, [[United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon|United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL)]], [[Operation Active Endeavour|Active Endeavour]], and Evacuation Operation from Libya as a Tactical Commander or Commanding Officer.\n\n== Awards ==\n[[File:Admiral Ugurlu having his award for becoming the first at Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition from Admiral Yigit,Chief of Navy.jpg|left|thumb|Admiral Ugurlu (right) having his award for becoming the first at Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition]]\nHe is well known with his breakthrough data science projects. He has won \u201cThe Innovative Research Project Competition\u201d twice with his Big Data and Artificial Intelligence (AI) related projects.\n\n1998, The honor of degree of Naval War College by Turkish Prime Minister Mr. [[Mesut Y\u0131lmaz]]\n\n1999, The article 5 [[NATO]] medal for service with NATO in relation to Active Endeavour Operations\n\n2000, The NATO Medal for service with NATO in relation to [[Kosovo]] Operations\n\n2000, The NATO Medal for service with NATO in relation to Former [[Yugoslavia]] Operations\n\n2007, Became the third in the 3rd Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition with his \"Digital Sail and [[Ship gun fire-control system|Fire Control System]]\" project.\n\n2011, Became the first in the 5th Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition with his \"National Digital Operational Analysis System\" project.\n\n== End of his Navy career ==\n\nHe was in NATO Headquarters/Norfolk-USA when the failed coup attempt started in Turkey on 15 July 2016. He was being called by the ruling party AKP during ongoing series of [[2016\u201317 purges in Turkey|purges]] enabled by a [[Martial law and state of emergency in Turkey|state of emergency]] after the [[2016 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat attempt|15 July failed coup d'\u00e9tat]]. His duty and service ended with an emergency decree<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hukukmedeniyeti.org/haber/10762/ohal-in-2-khk-si-yayinladi-iste-tam-metni/|title=OHAL'\u0130n 2. KHK's\u0131 yay\u0131nlad\u0131. \u0130\u015fte tam metni - Hukuk Medeniyeti|website=Hukukmedeniyeti.org|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.resmigazete.gov.tr/eskiler/2016/07/20160727M2..htm|title=Ba\u015fbakanl\u0131k Mevzuat\u0131 Geli\u015ftirme ve Yay\u0131n Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc|website=www.resmigazete.gov.tr|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> on 29 July 2016 with more than 200K [[Turkish Armed Forces|Turkish military service]], as well as various [[Ministries of Turkey|civil servants]] and private businesses. He could not turn back to his country. Residing in the US <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dw.com/en/report-purged-turkish-admiral-seeks-asylum-in-us/a-19463141|title=Report: Purged Turkish admiral seeks asylum in US {{!}} News {{!}} DW {{!}} 10.08.2016|last=(www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche Welle|website=DW.COM|language=en|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/08/10/489506041/turkish-admiral-sought-in-failed-coup-may-be-seeking-asylum-in-u-s-officials-say|title=Turkish Admiral Sought In Failed Coup May Be Seeking Asylum In U.S., Officials Say|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-01-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\n\nGraduated with distinction from Armed Forces Staff College \u2013 Istanbul, 2008\n\nGraduated with distinction from Naval War College \u2013 Istanbul, 1998\n\nBachelor of Science: Electric-Electronics, Naval Academy \u2013 Istanbul, 1986\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ugurlu, Mustafa Zeki}}\n[[Category:Turkish admirals]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military person\n| name          = Rear Admiral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu\n| image         = Admiaral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu.jpg\n| birth_date    = September 4, 1965\n| birth_place   = [[Hakkari]], Turkey\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nickname      = \n| allegiance    = {{flag|Turkey}}\n| branch        = {{flagicon image|Flag of Turkish Naval Forces Command.PNG|size=18px}} [[Turkish Navy]]\n| serviceyears  = 1986\u20132016\n| rank          = [[Rear admiral]]\n| commands      = Turkish Mine Group<br>4th Destroyer Division<br>TCG Zafer (USS Tomas C. Hart)\n| battles       = [[Operation Active Endeavour]]<br>[[United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon]]<br>[[Operation Unified Protector]]\n| awards        = 3rd The Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition<br>5th The Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition\n| website       = \n}}\n\n'''Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu''' was a [[Two-star rank|two-star]] [[Rear admiral|admiral]] in the [[Turkish Naval Forces|Turkish Navy]] who recently served as a [[flag officer]] at [[NATO]] [[Allied Command Transformation|Supreme Allied Command Transformation]] in [[Norfolk, Virginia|Norfolk]]-[[United States|USA]].\n[[File:Admiral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu.jpg|right|thumb|250px|Admiral Mustafa Zeki Ugurlu CO, Thomas C Heart (TCG ZAFER)]]\n\n== Navy career ==\n\nHe has been promoted to Rear Admiral (LH) in 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/turkey/2011/08/05/yas-promotes-36-generals-and-admirals-to-higher-rank|title=YA\u015e promotes 36 generals and admirals to higher rank|work=DailySabah|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> and Rear Admiral (UH) in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/2015-yuksek-askeri-sura-yas-kararlarini-acikladi-yas-kararlarinda-atama-alan-kisiler-kimler-29735528|title=2015 Y\u00fcksek Askeri \u015eura (YA\u015e) kararlar\u0131n\u0131 a\u00e7\u0131klad\u0131! YA\u015e kararlar\u0131nda atama alan ki\u015filer kimler?|work=H\u00fcrriyet|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr}}</ref> Before his last assignment in NATO,  He has served as Head of Communication and Information Systems Department<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.haber7.com/guncel/haber/911273-hangi-komutan-hangi-goreve-atandi-tam-liste|title=Hangi komutan hangi g\u00f6reve atand\u0131, tam liste|last=Haber7|website=Haber7|language=tr|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> between 2011 and 2012, Head of Personnel Department<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.haberler.com/atama-kararlari-11-3839329-haberi/|title=Atama Kararlar\u0131|work=Haberler.com|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr-TR}}</ref> between 2012-2013, and the Commander of Turkish Mine Group between 2013-2015.  He commanded [[Ottoman minelayer Nusret|Nusret]] 2013<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ege-sularinda-nefes-kesen-tatbikat-27657028|title=Ege sular\u0131nda nefes kesen tatbikat|work=H\u00fcrriyet|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr}}</ref> and Nusret 2014<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.denizhaber.com.tr/denizlerimizde-1-dunya-savasindan-kalma-200un-uzerinde-mayin-var-haber-58932.htm|title=Denizlerimizde 1. D\u00fcnya Sava\u015f\u0131'ndan kalma 200'\u00fcn \u00fczerinde may\u0131n var'|work=Deniz Haber|access-date=2018-01-24|language=tr-TR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/nusret-2014-nefes-kesti-izmir-yerelhaber-493278/|title=NUSRET-2014 NEFES KEST\u0130|last=sitesi|first=milliyet.com.tr T\u00fcrkiye'nin lider haber|website=M\u0130LL\u0130YET HABER - T\u00dcRK\u0130YE'N\u0130N HABER S\u0130TES\u0130|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> international [[Minelaying|Mine Warfare]] exercises.\n\nAs a [[surface warfare officer]], he was assigned as Commanding Officer of TCG Zafer ([[USS Thomas C. Hart (FF-1092)|USS Tomas C. Hart]]) between 2005-2007 and Commander of 4th Destroyer Division between 2010-2011. He participated in the [[Operation Active Endeavour]] in 2006, [[United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon]] (UNIFIL) in 2007 and [[2011 military intervention in Libya|Non-Combatants Evacuation Operation of Libya]] in 2011.\n\nAshore, Ugurlu served at [[NATO]], [[Turkish General Staff]] and [[Turkish Naval Forces]] Headquarters as Naval Project & Planning Officer. During his NATO [[Allied Joint Force Command Naples|Allied Joint Forces Command]] Naples-Italy tour, he participated [[NATO#Kosovo intervention|Kosovo]] and [[NATO intervention in Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnia-Herzeginova]] operations between 2000 and 2003.\n\nHis assignment included a role as inspector officer for [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)]], where he executed monitoring mission in old [[Eastern Bloc]] Countries and participated in international inspections. \n\n== NATO and International Career ==\n\nHe served as Assistant Chief of Staff of Command & Control, Deployability and Sustainability in [[Allied Command Transformation|NATO Supreme Allied Command Transformation in Norfolk]], USA between 2015 and 2016. He was responsible for NATO\u2019s Cyber Defense, Big Data, Artificial Intelligence, Communication Information Systems, Space, [[Federated Mission Networking]], Core Enterprise Services, Ballistic Missile Defense programs.\n[[File:Admiral Ugurlu, Replenishment at sea during Libya Evacuation Operation (TCG Gaziantep and ITS Etna).jpg|left|thumb]]\nHe was a member of key NATO executive boards, including Consultation Command Control Board (C3B), Agency Supervisory Board (ASB), Cyber Defense Management Board (CDMB), and Capability Package Board (CPB).\n\nHe was Naval Planning Officer in [[Allied Naval Forces Southern Europe|NATO-AFSOUTH-Napoli]] between 2000-2003, he was responsible for developing maritime capabilities on NATO naval bases and facilities in the Mediterranean.\n\nHe was assigned as an inspector officer for [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)]], monitoring missions in old Eastern Bloc Countries, as well as participated in international inspections with European partners between 1998-2000.\n\nHe have participated in international operations, [[United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon|United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL)]], [[Operation Active Endeavour|Active Endeavour]], and Evacuation Operation from Libya as a Tactical Commander or Commanding Officer.\n\n== Awards ==\n[[File:Admiral Ugurlu having his award for becoming the first at Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition from Admiral Yigit,Chief of Navy.jpg|left|thumb|Admiral Ugurlu (right) having his award for becoming the first at Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition]]\nHe is well known with his breakthrough data science projects. He has won \u201cThe Innovative Research Project Competition\u201d twice with his Big Data and Artificial Intelligence (AI) related projects.\n\n1998, The honor of degree of Naval War College by Turkish Prime Minister Mr. [[Mesut Y\u0131lmaz]]\n\n1999, The article 5 [[NATO]] medal for service with NATO in relation to Active Endeavour Operations\n\n2000, The NATO Medal for service with NATO in relation to [[Kosovo]] Operations\n\n2000, The NATO Medal for service with NATO in relation to Former [[Yugoslavia]] Operations\n\n2007, Became the third in the 3rd Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition with his \"Digital Sail and [[Ship gun fire-control system|Fire Control System]]\" project.\n\n2011, Became the first in the 5th Navy-wide Innovative Research Project Competition with his \"National Digital Operational Analysis System\" project.\n\n== End of his Navy career ==\n\nHe was in NATO Headquarters/Norfolk-USA when the failed coup attempt started in Turkey on 15 July 2016. He was being called by the ruling party AKP during ongoing series of [[2016\u201317 purges in Turkey|purges]] enabled by a [[Martial law and state of emergency in Turkey|state of emergency]] after the [[2016 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat attempt|15 July failed coup d'\u00e9tat]]. His duty and service ended with an emergency decree<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hukukmedeniyeti.org/haber/10762/ohal-in-2-khk-si-yayinladi-iste-tam-metni/|title=OHAL'\u0130n 2. KHK's\u0131 yay\u0131nlad\u0131. \u0130\u015fte tam metni - Hukuk Medeniyeti|website=Hukukmedeniyeti.org|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.resmigazete.gov.tr/eskiler/2016/07/20160727M2..htm|title=Ba\u015fbakanl\u0131k Mevzuat\u0131 Geli\u015ftirme ve Yay\u0131n Genel M\u00fcd\u00fcrl\u00fc\u011f\u00fc|website=www.resmigazete.gov.tr|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> on 29 July 2016 with more than 200K [[Turkish Armed Forces|Turkish military service]], as well as various [[Ministries of Turkey|civil servants]] and private businesses. He could not turn back to his country. Residing in the US <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dw.com/en/report-purged-turkish-admiral-seeks-asylum-in-us/a-19463141|title=Report: Purged Turkish admiral seeks asylum in US {{!}} News {{!}} DW {{!}} 10.08.2016|last=(www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche Welle|website=DW.COM|language=en|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/08/10/489506041/turkish-admiral-sought-in-failed-coup-may-be-seeking-asylum-in-u-s-officials-say|title=Turkish Admiral Sought In Failed Coup May Be Seeking Asylum In U.S., Officials Say|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-01-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\n\nGraduated with distinction from Armed Forces Staff College \u2013 Istanbul, 2008\n\nGraduated with distinction from Naval War College \u2013 Istanbul, 1998\n\nBachelor of Science: Electric-Electronics, Naval Academy \u2013 Istanbul, 1986\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ugurlu, Mustafa Zeki}}\n[[Category:Turkish admirals]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Tansel9182", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(New rank)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mustafa_Zeki_Ugurlu"}
